    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.2: \"PDZ2 of SAP90/PSD-95 is able to precipitate a chimeric EphrinB1/Sema4F protein\"\n\nFig.3: \"EphrinB1/Sema4F, but not EphrinB1/Sema4FΔ, is able to translocate SAP90/PSD-95 from the cytosol to the membrane. \"\n\nFig.4: \"Sema4F immunoreactivity is present in synaptosome fractions and enriched in post-synaptic density fractions from rat brain\"\n\nFig.5: \"Colocalization of Sema4F with SAP90/PSD-95 and synapsin1 in cultured hippocampal neurons\"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - \"Hippocampal neurons from new-born (P0-P4) Wistar rats ...\"\n- \"Sema4F immunoreactivity is present in synaptosome fractions and enriched in post-synaptic density fractions from rat brain\"\n- \"To construct EphrinB1/Sema4F the cytoplasmic and transmembrane domain of Sema4F (amino acids 670-777, nucleotides 2088-2412) was amplified using the primer TTCTTC AACTCCAAGACCGTTGTGGGGGCTGGGCTG and the primer up from a cDNA clone representing almost the complete coding sequence of mouse Sema4F isolated from a screen of a mouse brain cDNA library (Clontech). \"",
